Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC Buys The Home Depot Inc, Sells Exxon Mobil Corp, Verizon ...


July 13, 2017, 01:38:01 PM EDT
By insider, GuruFocus









































Shutterstock photo


Stonehearth Capital Management, LLCNew Purchases: HD ,Added Positions: BSV , AOA , PSK, AAPL,Reduced Positions:VWO, DBEF, VEA, VB, FM, IJH, SPHQ, GE, EEMV, XOM,For the details of Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC's stock buys and sells, go to http://www.gurufocus.com/StockBuy.php?GuruName=Stonehearth+Capital+Management%2C+LLCThese are the top 5 holdings of Stonehearth Capital Management, LLCVanguard FTSE Emerging Markets ( VWO ) - 272,177 shares, 15.71% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 5.2%Vanguard FTSE Developed Markets ( VEA ) - 219,203 shares, 12.8% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 4.55%Deutsche X-trackers MSCI EAFE Hedged Equity ( DBEF ) - 253,748 shares, 10.77% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 6.34%Vanguard Small-Cap ETF - DNQ ( VB ) - 54,690 shares, 10.48% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 5.12%iShares MSCI Frontier 100 Fund ( FM ) - 253,067 shares, 10.23% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 3.9%New Purchase: The Home Depot Inc (HD)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC initiated holdings in The Home Depot Inc. The purchase prices were between $145.91 and $158.81, with an estimated average price of $153.29. The stock is now traded at around $153.30. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.29%. The holdings were 1,350 shares as of 2017-06-30.Reduced: Exxon Mobil Corp (XOM)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC reduced to the holdings in Exxon Mobil Corp by 20.69%. The sale prices were between $79.5 and $83.49, with an estimated average price of $81.84. The stock is now traded at around $81.00. The impact to the portfolio due to this sale was -0.2%. Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC still held 6,741 shares as of 2017-06-30.Reduced: Verizon Communications Inc (VZ)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC reduced to the holdings in Verizon Communications Inc by 27.14%. The sale prices were between $44.41 and $49.31, with an estimated average price of $46.65. The stock is now traded at around $43.31. The impact to the portfolio due to this sale was -0.19%. Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC still held 7,672 shares as of 2017-06-30.HD 15-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of HDPeter Lynch Chart of HDPremium MembersThis article first appeared on GuruFocus .



