Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC Buys iShares Core S&P Mid-Cap, SPDR Wells Fargo ...


April 12, 2017, 01:38:03 PM EDT
By insider, GuruFocus









































Shutterstock photo


Stonehearth Capital Management, LLCNew Purchases: PSK , NEN ,Added Positions: IJH , VB, AOK, AOA, VZ,Reduced Positions:FM, VEA, DBEF, SPHQ, GE, VWO, AOR, CWB, EEMV, BSV,Sold Out:TIP, TLT, UTX,For the details of Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC's stock buys and sells, go to http://www.gurufocus.com/StockBuy.php?GuruName=Stonehearth+Capital+Management%2C+LLCThese are the top 5 holdings of Stonehearth Capital Management, LLCVanguard FTSE Emerging Markets ( VWO ) - 287,105 shares, 15.68% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 1.16%Vanguard FTSE Developed Markets ( VEA ) - 229,656 shares, 12.41% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 1.68%Deutsche X-trackers MSCI EAFE Hedged Equity ( DBEF ) - 270,931 shares, 11.02% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 1.89%Vanguard Small-Cap ETF - DNQ ( VB ) - 57,643 shares, 10.56% of the total portfolio. Shares added by 1.38%iShares MSCI Frontier 100 Fund ( FM ) - 263,336 shares, 10.04% of the total portfolio. Shares reduced by 2.48%New Purchase: SPDR Wells Fargo Preferred Stock (PSK)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC initiated holdings in SPDR Wells Fargo Preferred Stock. The purchase prices were between $41.95 and $44.08, with an estimated average price of $43.51. The stock is now traded at around $44.41. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 2.34%. The holdings were 38,788 shares as of 2017-03-31.New Purchase: New England Realty Associates LP (NEN)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC initiated holdings in New England Realty Associates LP. The purchase prices were between $59.97 and $69, with an estimated average price of $63.64. The stock is now traded at around $66.05. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 0.29%. The holdings were 3,022 shares as of 2017-03-31.Added: iShares Core S&P Mid-Cap (IJH)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC added to the holdings in iShares Core S&P Mid-Cap by 384.20%. The purchase prices were between $165.34 and $175.41, with an estimated average price of $170.12. The stock is now traded at around $169.70. The impact to the portfolio due to this purchase was 6.09%. The holdings were 32,606 shares as of 2017-03-31.Sold Out: iShares TIPS Bond (TIP)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC sold out the holdings in iShares TIPS Bond. The sale prices were between $112.62 and $114.96, with an estimated average price of $113.92.Sold Out: iShares 20+ Year Treasury Bond ETF (TLT)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC sold out the holdings in iShares 20+ Year Treasury Bond ETF. The sale prices were between $116.51 and $122.58, with an estimated average price of $120.Sold Out: United Technologies Corp (UTX)Stonehearth Capital Management, LLC sold out the holdings in United Technologies Corp. The sale prices were between $108.18 and $113.68, with an estimated average price of $111.49.IJH 15-Year Financial DataThe intrinsic value of IJHPeter Lynch Chart of IJHPremium MembersThis article first appeared on GuruFocus .



